[b]Modern Wyckoff State Machine Lite[/b] is a lightweight Wyckoff phase overlay that tracks accumulation, distribution, markup and markdown context in real time.

[b]What it does[/b]

The indicator qualifies trading ranges with ADX and ATR-normalized range width, then scores accumulation versus distribution evidence from range location, event memory, absorption, midline behavior and structure. A state machine maps that evidence into Wyckoff phases A-E and displays the current read directly on the chart.

[b]Key features[/b]

[list]
[*]Accumulation, Distribution, Markup and Markdown state tracking
[*]A-E phase model with configurable minimum phase duration
[*]Quality-graded Spring, UTAD, SOS, SOW, LPS and LPSY event labels
[*]Stored Spring/UTAD retest logic using event price and event volume
[*]Pivot-confirmed LPS and LPSY with pivot-bar volume checks
[*]Selling Climax / Buying Climax and absorption context
[*]Range high, midpoint and low visualization
[*]Locked trading range after phase start
[*]Range-bounded phase rectangles with state/phase labels and old-zone display modes
[*]Phase-track line inside the active trading range
[*]Cause Score for Phase B context
[*]Dashboard with accumulation score, distribution score, cause score, confidence and range quality
[*]Alerts for key events and Phase E trend release
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]

[list]
[*]Use the range lines to judge the active operating area.
[*]Use the labeled phase rectangles and phase track as the current Wyckoff context.
[*]Use the dashboard scores to compare accumulation, distribution and cause-building evidence.
[*]Treat event labels as context markers, not standalone entry signals.
[/list]

